  "text": "Therapeutic strategies, such as the use of trastuzumab and other tyrosine kinase inhibitors, have already been approved for targeted treatment of cancer. This targeted therapy is currently limited to certain cancers in clinical practice. The blockade of EGFR as an important therapeutical intervention alone and in combination with chemotherapy has already been investigated in soft tissue sarcomas (including uterine leiomyosarcomas) using in vitro and in vivo (animal model) experiments with promising results [CITATION_1] . Our findings further support these results and highlight a role for EGFR and especially for the activation by phosphorylation of Y845, as far as uterine leiomyosarcoma is concerned.",
